evidence.text: Hearing on Plaintiff's Expedited Motion for TRO and preliminary Injunction set for 8/6/2025 09:00 AM in Miami Division before Judge Kathleen M. Williams.

add_extracted.value: Preliminary Injunction Hearing scheduled for August 6, 2025, 9:00 AM in Miami Division before Judge Kathleen M. Williams

evidence.text: Over four days of evidentiary presentation and oral argument between August 6 and August 13, 2025, the Court heard testimony from ten witnesses and viewed over a hundred exhibits.
After hearing additional argument, the Court granted Plaintiffs’ narrow request for a TRO, halting further expansion of the site for fourteen days.

extracted.value: Preliminary Injunction Hearing held August 6, 7, 12, and 13, 2025, with Temporary Restraining Order granted August 7, 2025, halting further expansion of the detention site for fourteen days

PAPERLESS Minute Entry for proceedings held before Judge Kathleen M. Williams. Miscellaneous Hearing held on 8/13/2025. Court heard oral arguments. Counsel of record present. Court Reporter: Patricia Diaz, 305-523-5178 / Patricia_Diaz@flsd.uscourts.gov. (mso) (Entered: 08/13/2025)

At 8:47 p.m. on August 21—the last day of the TRO period—the court entered a preliminary injunction requiring Defendants to (i) immediately cease bringing new detainees to the facility, (ii) immediately cease new construction, and (iii) remove all new lighting, fencing, and utilities within sixty days—effectively shuttering the facility. Doc. 131 80-81.
